;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;If you look at Puranas and =\r\nTantras, so much of the knowledge was taught by Shiva to Parvati (or vice v=\r\nersa). Shiva is of course a great scholar and expert in all things you ment=\r\nioned when questioning Hanuman being Shiva tattva (&quot;an expert in all forms =\r\nof music, expert in poetry, expert in grammer/logic, expert in speech, a pu=\r\nndit of the highest order, a very multifaceted character&quot;).&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Al=\r\nso, consider the imagery of Shiva being fiercely angry when his wife Sati b=\r\neing insulting and giving up her life and Shiva wreaking havoc on Daksha&#39;s =\r\nyajnashala. Does that come across as detachment to you? You quoted incident=\r\ns from Rama&#39;s life like crying for Sita to question his &quot;detachment&quot;. Thoug=\r\nh such incidents in Rama&#39;s life do go against cliched understanding of deta=\r\nchment and Shiva tattva, you have to realize that Shiva himself had similar=\r\n incidents.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Sub-consciously,\n some people may associate detach=\r\nment with disinterest or aloofness or not caring or inaction. That is incor=\r\nrect. Detachment is internal. It is possible to be calm and stone-faced ext=\r\nernally, while there is deep attachment internally. It is also possible to =\r\nbehave angrily or passionately while there is no attachment in the heart. D=\r\netachment is an internal state and not a property of external signs. When y=\r\nou are looking at actions of higher beings, be more aware of this. Most imp=\r\nortantly, if one starts taking things with deep esoteric meaning at a super=\r\nficial external level, one will start having all confusions.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;It is not that Shiva does not care or is disinte=\r\nrested in worldly things. After all, he is the reservoir of potential energ=\r\ny that runs the cosmos. Shakti extracts energy from him and puts it to use =\r\nby converting into kinetic\n energy.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Now, Shiva is disintereste=\r\nd in the sense that he absolutely does not care for what purpose the energy=\r\n is used by Shakti. Whatever it is, he unfailingly and uncomplainingly prov=\r\nides Shakti with the energy she needs.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;You can look at Shakti =\r\nas an aspect of Shiva that puts *his* energy to use and you can also look S=\r\nhiva as an aspect of Shakti that stores *her* energy. They are a team that =\r\nwork together managing this field of duality and inseparable really. They c=\r\nan be viewed as one also.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;As soul =\r\nis a spark of Shiva tattva and mind is a spark of shakti tattva, the same h=\r\nolds in the case of soul and mind of individual beings. Soul provides the s=\r\nupport mind needs for its various pursuits. Whatever activity one engages i=\r\nn, it is not possible without the willing support of soul. But it is happen=\r\ning because mind\n envisioned it and wanted it. Again, soul and mind are a t=\r\neam and two sides of the same coin of individual consciousness.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;All of us do have soul and mind. Rama and Krishna also had them. But my p=\r\noint was that Rama&#39;s life is a story representation of how an individual so=\r\nul operates at an esoteric level and serves its purpose. Similarly, Krishna=\r\n&#39;s life is a story representation of how a perfected mind operates at an es=\r\noterical level and serves its purpose.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;br&gt;One disagreement we had was w.r.t. &quot;full&quot; avataras. Just to re-iterate=\r\n, I don&#39;t believe in &quot;full&quot; avataras as you envision. In the analogy below,=\r\n Ganga water is paramatmamsa and tap water is jivatmamsa.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Many=\r\n vessels may contain tap water with a few drops of Ganga water added (a nor=\r\nmal being). Some vessels may contain 40% tap water and 60% Ganga water (ams=\r\navatara).\n Some rare vessels may contain 100% Ganga water (poornavatara). B=\r\nut no vessel can contain &quot;Full Ganga&quot;, which can only flow outside and not =\r\nfit in any vessel! The reason you take Ganga water in a vessel is for a spe=\r\ncific purpose and you just take a vessel that suits the purpose.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;Same thing holds with avataras. Ethereal beings exist in their &quot;full&quot; fo=\r\nrm ethereally. When they take a form on earth, it is what suffices the purp=\r\nose. It is like a vessel holding Ganga water.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;If the vessel it=\r\nself claims &quot;don&#39;t think that I am this vessel, I am Ganga water itself&quot;, i=\r\nt is not incorrect. But it is also not correct if you understand that that =\r\nparticular vessel is the best and contains &quot;full Ganga&quot;.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Now let me extend this analogy to the basic disagree=\r\nment that started this whole discussion.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;There were 9 vessels.=\r\n\n First vessel was very small (fish form). Next vessel was bigger (more evo=\r\nlved turtle form). Next vessel is bigger (boar). Next vessel was even bigge=\r\nr (half-man). Next vessel was bigger (full man, but dwarf). Next vessel was=\r\n bigger (full man, but passionate). Next vessel was bigger. Next vessel was=\r\n the same size, but had a very nice design and some praised it as &quot;Ganga wa=\r\nter itself&quot;. Next vessel was the same size, but having very plain design.&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Someone (Rajarshi) came along and said, &quot;I see a clear pattern =\r\nof evolution of purity. So the last vessel does not belong. Throw it out.&quot; =\r\nHe also said that the 8th vessel was Ganga itself.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Someone els=\r\ne (Narasimha) came along and said, &quot;well, vessels 3, 4, 7 and 8 are filled =\r\nwith 100% Ganga water, while vessels 5 and 6 are not. Don&#39;t conclude that a=\r\nbout purity from the outside and look inside.&quot; He also said that no vessel =\r\nwas Ganga itself, though 4 vessels contained 100% Ganga\n water.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Let me be absolutely clear about one thing. T=\r\nhough it may have seemed like Rajarshi was batting for Krishna and I for Ra=\r\nma, I do not have such divisions in my mind. Though Shiva &amp; Shakti or s=\r\noul &amp; mind play slightly different roles, I see them as two aspects of =\r\na single manifestation. In fact, I suggest that one cannot understand Shiva=\r\n tattva perfectly without also understanding Shakti tattva perfectly, and v=\r\nice versa. I will in fact say the same thing about Rama tattva and Krishna =\r\ntattva.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Also, I always like focusing on the boundaries of diff=\r\nerences of opinion with like-minded people, to improve collective understan=\r\nding.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; I rest my case!-:)&lt;br&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;br&gt;Yes Rajarshi, your &quot;case&quot; is really\n tired from jumping all over t=\r\nhe place frantically and do please give it some &quot;rest&quot;! ;-)&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Se=\r\nriously though, I share my thoughts with you not because my knowledge is pe=\r\nrfect or superior, but because sharing what I see may oneday contribute tow=\r\nards perfect knowledge in *someone*. There are some really sincere seekers =\r\nof Arsha Vidya here. You are especially at the forefront of them, Rajarshi.=\r\n So I respectfully, humbly and lovingly submit my confident, but fallible, =\r\nviews.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Best wishes for Rishi Panchami again!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Best=\r\n regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resource=\r\ns: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/di=\r\nv&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\r\n---1593584224-127308093-1368583083=:58782--\r\n\n"}}